    "Id": "120733",
    "ThreadId": "36392",
    "Html": "<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Hi,</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"color:#1f497d\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt -1.2pt\"><span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">You may add a Title property in the Presenter or Presentation Model (depending in the approach you are using) of your Shell, which you change when necessary, and then you would only need to do data binding between this property and the Title property in the XAML.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt -1.2pt\"><span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt -1.2pt\"><span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">You may find interesting this blog post that describes how to use Presentation Model and Data Templates: </span><a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/jdominguez/2008/09/presentation-model-with-datatemplates-in-compositewpf-prism-sample/\"><span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-family:Calibri\">Presentation Model with DataTemplates in CompositeWPF (Prism) Sample</span></a><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt -1.2pt\"><span style=\"color:#1f497d\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt -1.2pt\"><span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Hope it helps.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Ignacio Baumann Fonay</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt -0.6pt\"><span><a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/ibaumann/\"><span style=\"color:#0000ff;font-family:Calibri\">http://blogs.southworks.net/ibaumann/</span></a></span></p>\r\n",
